      • getEigensystemSolution

        public static void getEigensystemSolution(int dim,
                          org.ejml.alg.dense.decomposition.EigenDecomposition<org.ejml.data.DenseMatrix64F> eigdec,
                          org.ejml.data.DenseMatrix64F eigvals,
                          org.ejml.data.DenseMatrix64F eigvecs)
        Gets a more succinct version of the solution of an eigensystem. It is assumed that no imaginary eigenvalues are present, and that the system has already been solved by eigdec.decompose(...).
        Parameters:
        dim - the dimension of the system, i.e., as dim*dim matrix.
        eigDec - the solved eigensystem.
        eigvals - output vector where to store eigenvalues. Should have size (dim,1).
        eigvecs - output matrix where to store eigenvectors column-wise. Should have size (dim,dim).

        Computes element-wise b_i=exp(a_i*alpha) for each element i.
        Parameters:
        dim - number of elements.
        a - matrix with size dim.
        alpha - multiplier.
        b - output matrix with size dim.

      • multDiagA

        public static void multDiagA(int dim,
             org.ejml.data.DenseMatrix64F a,
             org.ejml.data.DenseMatrix64F b,
             org.ejml.data.DenseMatrix64F c)
        Computes c=a*b where a is a (compacted) diagonal matrix and b is a (typically) dense matrix.
        Parameters:
        dim - size of uncompacted a is (dim,dim).
        a - diagonal matrix in 'compacted' form. Should have size (dim,1).
        b - dense matrix. Should have size (dim,k).
        c - output matrix. Should have size (dim,k).
